title: Lion Journals—Pair
description:
Journals developed from Edward Kemeys’ Lions, 1893, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection. 

Perfect for keeping a diary, notes, and musing.  One journal features a large image of a single lion, while the other journal’s cover is a grid of smaller lions.

  • 2 Journals.
  • Dimensions: 7 x 5 in.
  • 64 pages – lined.
  • Printed paper with machine sewn binding.
